BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (09): FRANCE, BOVINE, OVINE, SEROTYPE 8, SPREAD, OIE
************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 25 Sep 2015
Source: La France Agricole [in French, machine trans., edited]
http://www.lafranceagricole.fr/actualite-agricole/fco-la-zone-reglementee-s-etend-au-sud-est-carte-110028.html


The Ministry of Agriculture has modified on Friday morning [25 Sep 2015] the dimensions of the zoning in place since the appearance of bluetongue in Allier. This followed the publication, on 24 Sep 2015, in the Official Journal, of virological tests obtained by the national reference laboratory ANSES and the accredited laboratory network on 23 Sep 2015. The restricted zone (composed of the protection and surveillance zones) has been extended. The initially affected departments (Allier, Creuse, Puy de Dome and the Indre) now include also the Loire and Haute-Loire. Part of the Ardeche, Isere, Drome and some towns in the north of the Gard are now part of the surveillance zone [a map showing the new zoning is available at the source URL].

This decree also formalizes the opening of the vaccination campaign against BTV [bluetongue virus] serotype 8 in France [excluding Corsica where vaccination has been applied earlier; see comment].

The categories of animals to be vaccinated as a priority are:
- Ruminant animals kept in holdings subject to a decree on declaration of infection following confirmation of the presence of bluetongue;
- Ruminant animals intended for trade or export;
- Ruminant animals belonging to epidemiologically strategic establishments such as insemination centers, experimental stations and individual monitoring stations.

